We believe that this manuscript is particularly suitable for Ecology Letters because it provides new results on an issue that is both of broad interest to ecologists and also of interest to policymakers: the detection of early warning signs for regime shifts (such as eutrophication or more complex shifts).   We recognize that this is a very active area, and argue that our contribution is truly novel and important as  }{\i\ai\rtlch \ltrch\loch
we are the first to quantify the important trade-off between false positives and missed signals for early warning signs.  While the problem of quantifying uncertainty has been largely avoided in a literature that has relied on direct comparisons with control systems, experimental replicates, or the knowledge of hindsight, such luxuries will not be available in natural systems, which will require robust uncertainty quantification. }{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\ql\aspalpha\faauto\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\nowidctlpar{\*\hyphen2\hyphlead2\hyphtrail2\hyphmax0}\kerning1\hich\af4\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\lang1081\cf0\loch\f0\fs24\lang1033\li0\ri0\lin0\rin0\fi0\ltrpar{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
